17:
Heed me, stars! Unravel what stands
before us!
21:
Unravel our curse, that we may yet
again find hope!
28:
By the time we had returned from
the Palace of Stars, we found that
the brisk winter weather was
coming to an end.
31: Before we knew it, spring had come.
34:
They say that spring is the season of
endings... and of new beginnings.
40:
Ugh. Again? But we JUST got back
from exploring the abyss.
44:
There isn't actually a whole lot left to
"explore" at this point. We know
where to go. All we need to do is
warp to the other world, bust some
heads, and head back home!
48:
We'll have plenty of time. We're
scheduled to be back the day
before the ceremony.
61:
That's right, both ours and Nao's.
And the students from Voluntas, too.
66:
You know that "grand reopening"
thing they've been talking about?
Yeah, Mr. Takamori pitched the idea
of doing the graduation on the
same day.
70:
Nao... You're giving the speech at
the ceremony, right?
73:
...That means you better not be late.
Make sure Marina knows about it,
okay?
78:
Duh, Yumu! I'm way more on top of
things than you are, you know. But I
was wondering...
82:
Don't you want to come along on
the expedition, too?
87:
Well... It's my eye. I don't think it'll
ever go back to the way it was
before.
93:
...Says the guy that tried fighting
with one eye and got his ass
handed to him by that Kaleido Beast.
97:
Yeah, I sure wasn't expecting that.
And Nimbus wasn't happy with me
either, to say the least...
101:
That's an understatement. I've never
seen Nimbus that mad before...
118:
I'm gonna cut RIGHT to the chase!
We don't have anywhere near
enough materials to build our
ultimate golem for the graduation
ceremony!
123:
...HEY! This is a BIG deal! I'll have you
remember that this is MY
graduation we're talking about!
What's with the cold shoulder?!
128:
D-Dedalia, please! Golems are
important and all, but there's
something much more grave that
we need to discuss...
131:
We've... run out of supplies! We don't
have what we need for the rest of
the ceremony, let alone a golem!
135:
So the fate of your grand "Ceremony
of Graduation" hangs in the balance!
